### HYMN XLIV

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_2004401">1</span></span>Praise Indra
whom our songs must laud, great Sovran of man-  
   kind, the Chief  
  Most liberal who controlleth men.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_2004402">2</span></span>In whom the
hymns of praise delight, and all the glory-giving  
   songs,  
  Like the flood's longing for the sea. <span id="page_303">p.
303</span>  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_2004403">3</span></span>Him I invite
with eulogy, best King, effective in the fight,  
  Strong for the gain of mighty spoil.

